Workaround for static-destructor-order crash in hyprlock 0.9.5.

When hyprlock fails to bind ext-session-lock-v1 or fails to acquire the
session lock, it calls exit(1). That triggers the C++ runtime's static
destructor chain, during which CSCDMAFrame::~CSCDMAFrame() calls
eglDestroyImage(g_pEGL->eglDisplay, m_image). g_pEGL is a namespace-scope
std::unique_ptr<CEGL> whose underlying CEGL has already been destroyed by
the time the frame's destructor runs; the unique_ptr's internal raw
pointer is left in a freed-but-non-null state (post-delete null-assignment
is elided), so the null check passes and the deref of g_pEGL->eglDisplay
segfaults.

Replacing exit(1) with _exit(1) on these failure paths skips static
destructors entirely, avoiding the crash without altering the intended
process termination semantics (we are bailing out before the lock UI ever
appears -- nothing useful to flush or clean up).

This is a workaround, not a root-cause fix. The proper fix is upstream
(make ~CSCDMAFrame validate the EGL display, or explicitly tear down image
caches before exit). See diagnosis in dotfiles git history.

--- a/src/core/hyprlock.cpp
+++ b/src/core/hyprlock.cpp
@@ -341,7 +341,7 @@

     if (!m_sWaylandState.sessionLock) {
         Log::logger->log(Log::CRIT, "Couldn't bind to ext-session-lock-v1, does your compositor support it?");
-        exit(1);
+        _exit(1);
     }

     // Gather info about monitors
@@ -371,7 +371,7 @@
         m_sLoopState.timerEvent = true;
         m_sLoopState.timerCV.notify_all();
         g_pAuth->terminate();
-        exit(1);
+        _exit(1);
     }

     const auto fingerprintAuth = g_pAuth->getImpl(AUTH_IMPL_FINGERPRINT);
